channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: JD Vance Energizes Rallygoers During Western Trail Swing to Glendale, Arizona
House conservative who's twice moved to impeach Vice President Harris faces competitive GOP primary
item.description: A conservative congressman who has twice filed articles of impeachment against Vice President Kamala Harris is grabbing national attention as Tennessee holds primary elections on Tuesday.

item.title: Trump-Backed John McGuire's Primary Victory Over Va. Rep. Bob Good in Recount
item.description: A Republican primary recount is being held Thursday to settle whether John McGuire, a state senator backed by former President Donald Trump, narrowly defeated incumbent Rep. Bob Good, R-Va., a conservative who chairs the hard-right House Freedom Caucus.

item.title: US Army Seeks Refund from Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson and the UFL As Sponsorship Led to Recruitment Falling
Unpacking the Supreme Court: Why it’s not just a MAGA stronghold, and how the justices really vote
item.description: The Supreme Court’s 2023 term reveals complex dynamics beyond a simple MAGA stronghold with nuanced voting patterns altering the ideological balance.

item.title: Blaine Holt to Newsmax: 'No Reverse Gear' in Middle East War
item.description: Retired Air Force Brig. Gen. Blaine Holt told Newsmax on Wednesday that things are escalating in the Middle East between Israel and Iran and "there's no reverse gear at this point in time."

item.title: Biden's Pentagon Approves Plea Deal for 9/11 Conspirators but Won't Tell the Terms of the Agreement
Trump vs. NABJ: Hostility and questions about journalism
item.description: Former President Trump took to the National Association of Black Journalists convention on Wednesday, which proved contentious for both himself and the hosting organization.

item.title: Snapchat Won't Reinstate Trump, Will Sell Him Ads
item.description: Snapchat has asked former President Donald Trump's campaign to advertise on the platform while simultaneously refusing to reinstate his account.

item.title: Abraham Hamadeh Wins Republican Primary for Arizona's 8th Congressional District
Trump assassination attempt: Supporters pumped after GOP nominee's comeback in Pennsylvania
item.description: Pumped up Trump supporters shared their elation and hope in the former president winning the 2024 election following a fiery Trump rally at Harrisburg’s New Holland Arena.

item.title: Vance Defends Trump's Comments on Harris' Heritage
item.description: Sen. J.D. Vance, R-Ohio, the GOP vice-presidential nominee, defended his running mate's controversial remarks about Vice President Kamala Harris' biracial heritage, describing the reaction as "hysterical" and characterizing Harris as a "chameleon."

item.title: WATCH: Donald Trump Delivers an All-Timer Re-Enacting Kamala Harris' Call With the Obamas
Alina Habba accuses Kamala Harris of 'committing a crime,' covering up Biden's health
item.description: Alina Habba, a legal spokesperson for former President Donald Trump, claimed at a rally that Vice President Kamala Harris committed a crime by "covering up" Biden's health.

item.title: Karoline Leavitt to Newsmax: Trump Took On Hostile ABC Host
item.description: Donald Trump gave a clinic on how to deal with a hostile media Wednesday, Trump campaign press secretary Karoline Leavitt told Newsmax.
